title: Walkin’ My Baby Back Home (Demo)
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Gee, it's great after being out late
Walking my baby back home
Arm in arm over meadow and farm
Walking my baby back home
[Verse 2]
We go along harmonizing a song
Or I'm reciting a poem
Owls go by and they give me the eye
Walking my baby back home
[Verse 4]
He's afraid of the dark
So I had to park outside of his door till light
He says if I try to kiss him, he'll cry
I dry his tears all through the night
[Chorus]
Hand in hand to a barbecue stand
Right from his doorway we roam
Eat sampling, it's a pleasure again
Walking my baby back home
[Instrumental Break]
